Redis Installation Steps


1. apt install redis-server -y
2. sudo systemctl start redis-server
3. sudo systemctl enable redis-server
4. redis-cli ping
5.  to make it accessible from outside
        a. sudo nano /etc/redis/redis.conf  --> bind 0.0.0.0 (by default it will be 127.0.0.1::*)

6. sudo systemctl restart redis-server


if you want to set password
1. sudo nano /etc/redis/redis.conf 
2. search for requirepass 
    a. uncomment and set the password --> requirepass new_password
3. sudo systemctl restart redis-server


check the connection 

1. redis-cli -h <host IP> -p 6379 -a <password>
2. ping
